### **GranTON Q3 Quarterly Report**

# ![][image1]2025 Q3 Tokamak Network Quarterly Report : 7/1 \~ 9/30

### **Highlight**

In Q3 2025, GranTON shifted from prototyping to operational readiness by prioritizing shipped, publicly usable pieces. Staking and DAO moved to community‑operable forms with DAO V2 documentation and tools, while the Tokamak Economics (RAT) line advanced with updated research and PoC testbeds. # **1\. Q3 2025 Grant Project Report**

This quarter the GranTON program shifted from prototyping to operational readiness. # **1.4 Developing Zero-Knowledge Proof-Based On-Demand Rollups([Overview](https://medium.com/tokamak-network/project-tokamak-zk-evm-67483656fd21)).**

### **Goal**  To provide an app that allows non-experts or non-developers to open and operate ZKP-based second-layer private channels.

### **Key Features**

* **Tokamak ZKP**  
  * A tool that allows anyone to easily convert Ethereum transactions into zero-knowledge proofs.  
  * No cloud server required, works even on low-spec laptops.  
  * Proof generation in less than 10 minutes.  
* **Tokamak ZKP channels**  
  * A tool that allows anyone to open and operate your own second-layer private channel as an application of the Tokamak ZKP.  
  * Update the state of Ethereum using zero-knowledge proofs generated on the private channel.  
  * To enhance your privacy.

### **Q3 Works**

# **1.5 Developing a Sybil-Resistance System for Decentralized Applications([Overview](https://tokamak.notion.site/03cc941223844f30ba4473e98b1275a7?pvs=25)).**

### **Goal**

Launch a Snapshot‑ready sybil‑resistance service based on TON staking. Build on‑chain contracts and reference tooling, stabilize sequencer/circuit packages, and prepare TRH integration so builders can gate actions using sybil‑aware scores.

### **Key Features**

* **CumulativeScore contract (staking amount \+ sybil score) for Snapshot policy gating.**  
* **Score‑simulator (Jupyter) to trial scoring rules and visualize impacts before governance votes.**  
* **Landing & Explorer for transparency and quick inspection.**  
* **Privacy‑preserving vouching protocol design to reduce sybil incentives without doxxing.**  
* **Backend/API & sequencer tools to support scoring and testing.**

### **Q3 Outputs**

* **Built a public tool for users/testers to experiment with how the scores change as the network evolves.**  
  * It can be used to add a link between two nodes and then display the recalculated scores for the network. This tool is designed to give users a better understanding of how the scoring algorithm works and a way to experiment with it. ([Link](https://mybinder.org/v2/gh/tokamak-network/syb-jupyter-notebooks/70d5992921de4e526111b42821bedcff911add29?urlpath=lab%2Ftree%2Frandom_walk_scoring_algorithm.ipynb))  
* **Developed the CumulativeScore Contract and deployed in sepolia**  
  * The CumulativeScore contract combines the staking amount from the Tokamak Staking protocol with Sybil scores to establish a unified scoring system to be used in Snapshot.([Link](https://github.com/tokamak-network/tokamak-sybil-resistance-mvp/blob/feat/add-cummulativescore/contracts/CummulativeScore_README.md))  
* **Wrote a Readme guide for integrating Snapshot with the SYB contract.** [(Link)](https://github.com/tokamak-network/tokamak-sybil-resistance-mvp/blob/feat/add-txn-data/contracts/README.md)  
* **Built a landing page.** ([Link](https://syb.network/))  
* **Built an explorer page for users to view the sequencer full state and to send transactions to the contract. (**[Link](https://explorer.syb.network/home))

**Q3 Summary and Next Steps**

In Q3, the team shipped user‑facing tools and an on‑chain CumulativeScore contract on testnet, plus guidance (Snapshot README, audit guide) and public touchpoints (landing/explorer, simulator). Next quarter, the team will resolve proof‑format changes needed for public testing, finalize the ECO combination formula, expose a TRH SDK hook and integration docs, and improve the Jupyter tool UX/docs to support pilots; then proceed with public trials and partner integrations.

####  **4\. Community**

#### **4.1 FAQ**

These are some of the FAQs from the community. Please check the section below.

* **What does it mean that the zk-EVM can convert random Ethereum transactions to zk-proofs?**

1. This milestone shows that Tokamak’s zk-EVM has reached the stage where arbitrary Ethereum transactions can be transformed into zero-knowledge proofs. All that is required is to provide a transaction as input to the system. The underlying theory of Tokamak zk-SNARK— the cryptographic engine powering the zk-EVM—ensures that the transaction can be faithfully replaced by a corresponding proof. This marks a major step toward building a fully functional zk-rollup, where transaction integrity is verifiable without revealing sensitive data. This advancement brings Tokamak closer to offering privacy-preserving execution of Ethereum smart contracts.  
* **What is the Tokamak Rollup Hub and why is it important?**

1. The **Tokamak Rollup Hub** (TRH) is an **on-demand Layer 2 infrastructure platform** designed to enable **seamless deployment** and **end-to-end lifecycle managemen**t of Appchains. It aims to serve as a comprehensive hub that not only showcases our research outputs but also offers **essential tools** for integration and smooth network operations by deployers. TRH supports various **modular rollup technologies** and **developer-friendly SDKs**. In this report, we would like to mention the successful completion of the **second round of testing for SDKv1**, marking significant progress toward a **community-ready release**.

* **Why do we need a Rollup Hub? Aren’t there already many Layer 2 solutions?**

1. The Tokamak Rollup Hub is more than just another **Layer 2 solution** — it’s a **flexible platform** that empowers developers to deploy **modular Layer 2 Appchains**, supporting various rollup types like **Optimistic and ZK Rollups**. It enables the integration of components such as bridges, explorers, cross-trade module, random number generator, fraud proofs, and data availability layers based on specific project needs, allowing for **fully customized rollup chains**. Deployed chains can be **self-managed** by deployers on their own AWS infrastructure (with support for more environments planned), removing the dependency on third-party RaaS providers.  
2. Instead of offering a one-size-fits-all rollup, Tokamak Rollup Hub provides the flexibility to **launch and manage your own rollup architecture** tailored to your application’s needs. In that sense, it’s not just a rollup — it’s a **platform for building rollups**.

* **How to contribute to the Tokamak Network?**

1. **Grant program**: create your own project and apply for [GranTON](https://www.notion.so/Tokamak-Network-Grant-Program-GranTON-f2384b458ea341a0987c7e73a909aa21?pvs=4)  
2. **Full time**: [apply for a full-time position](https://recruit.wanted.co.kr/p/QVxQS0MVRm5HWEpb) and earn salary in USDT/USDC in addition to the [TON](https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/tokamak-network) grant from the project.  
3. **Part time**: apply for a part-time by earning [TON](https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/tokamak-network) as a grant from project. Please contact the [project leader (owner)](https://www.notion.so/Tokamak-Network-Onboarding-523bc627bd374326b5dfbec3d3b0a8e1?pvs=21) directly and discuss with them.

* **How can I contact you if I would like to collaborate with the Tokamak Network team?**

  Thank you for your interest in collaborating with the Tokamak Network team. We are open to various forms of collaboration that foster Tokamak Network ecosystem growth and value.

  To discuss a potential collaboration, please send a brief description of your proposal to **hello@tokamak.network**, and we will review it and respond as soon as possible.
